Revision Date Notes
1.0.0 2014 Initial revision.
1.0.1 2016-08-03 Added AdvancedMediatek2 service that supports the configuration of MU-MIMO for each supported WiFi radio. Added the following:
  • struct MediatekAdvancedRadioSettings
  • action GetAdvancedSettings2
  • action SetAdvancedSettings2

Actions

GetAdvancedSettings

http://linksys.com/jnap/wirelessap/mediatek/GetAdvancedSettings
Get advanced radio settings specific to Mediatek platforms.

Note:

This action is safe to call within the context of a transaction.

Input Parameters

This action does not have any input parameters.

Output Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
isIGMPSnoopingEnabled bool no Is the Mediatek-specific behavior of IGMP snooping enabled?
isOBSSCoexsistenceEnabled bool no Is the Mediatek-specific behavior of overlapping BSS Coexistence enabled?
isEDCCAEnabled bool no Is the Mediatek-specific behavior of EDCCA enabled?

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/wirelessap/mediatek/GetAdvancedSettingsResult
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

Sample Transaction

POST [request-uri] HTTP/1.1
Host: 192.168.1.1
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in request body]
X-JNAP-Action: "http://linksys.com/jnap/wirelessap/mediatek/GetAdvancedSettings"

{
}
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in response body]

{
  "result": "OK",
  "output": {
    "isIGMPSnoopingEnabled": true,
    "isOBSSCoexsistenceEnabled": true,
    "isEDCCAEnabled": true
  }
}

GetAdvancedSettings2

http://linksys.com/jnap/wirelessap/mediatek/GetAdvancedSettings2
Get advanced radio settings specific to Mediatek platforms.

Note:

This action is safe to call within the context of a transaction.

Input Parameters

This action does not have any input parameters.

Output Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
isIGMPSnoopingEnabled bool no Is the Mediatek-specific behavior of IGMP snooping enabled?
isOBSSCoexsistenceEnabled bool no Is the Mediatek-specific behavior of overlapping BSS Coexistence enabled?
isEDCCAEnabled bool no Is the Mediatek-specific behavior of EDCCA enabled?
isMUMIMOSupported bool no Whether MU-MIMO is supported on the product.
advancedRadioSettings MediatekAdvancedRadioSettings[] yes Advanced settings for the Mediatek wireless radios. This parameter is returned when isMUMIMOSupported is true.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/wirelessap/mediatek/GetAdvancedSettings2Result
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

Sample Transaction

POST [request-uri] HTTP/1.1
Host: 192.168.1.1
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in request body]
X-JNAP-Action: "http://linksys.com/jnap/wirelessap/mediatek/GetAdvancedSettings2"

{
}
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in response body]

{
  "result": "OK",
  "output": {
    "isIGMPSnoopingEnabled": true,
    "isOBSSCoexsistenceEnabled": true,
    "isEDCCAEnabled": true,
    "isMUMIMOSupported": true,
    "advancedRadioSettings": [
      {
        "radioID": "RADIO_2.4GHz",
        "isMUMIMOEnabled": true
      }
    ]
  }
}

SetAdvancedSettings2

http://linksys.com/jnap/wirelessap/mediatek/SetAdvancedSettings2
Set advanced radio settings specific to Mediatek platforms.

Note:

This action is safe to call within the context of a transaction.

Input Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
isIGMPSnoopingEnabled bool no Is the Mediatek-specific behavior of IGMP snooping enabled?
isOBSSCoexsistenceEnabled bool no Is the Mediatek-specific behavior of overlapping BSS Coexistence enabled?
isEDCCAEnabled bool no Is the Mediatek-specific behavior of EDCCA enabled?
advancedRadioSettings MediatekAdvancedRadioSettings[] yes Advanced settings for the Mediatek wireless radios.

Output Parameters

This action does not have any output parameters.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/wirelessap/mediatek/SetAdvancedSettings2Result
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
ErrorMissingAdvancedRadioSettings The advancedRadioSettings parameter was not present, although MU-MIMO is supported.
ErrorUnknownRadio One of the specified radio IDs in advancedRadioSettings does not correspond to an actual radio in the access point.
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

Sample Transaction

POST [request-uri] HTTP/1.1
Host: 192.168.1.1
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in request body]
X-JNAP-Action: "http://linksys.com/jnap/wirelessap/mediatek/SetAdvancedSettings2"

{
  "isIGMPSnoopingEnabled": true,
  "isOBSSCoexsistenceEnabled": true,
  "isEDCCAEnabled": true,
  "advancedRadioSettings": [
    {
      "radioID": "RADIO_2.4GHz",
      "isMUMIMOEnabled": true
    }
  ]
}
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in response body]

{
  "result": "OK"
}

Structures

MediatekAdvancedRadioSettings

http://linksys.com/jnap/wirelessap/mediatek/MediatekAdvancedRadioSettings
This service provides access to Mediatek wireless driver settings. Advanced settings of a Mediatek wireless radio.

Structure Members

Member Name Type Optional Description
radioID string no The unique identifier of the radio.
isMUMIMOEnabled bool no Whether the Mediatek-specific behavior of MU-MIMO is enabled.
